  "name": "Simeoni 2004 preclinical xenograft PK/PD TGI model (transit-chain cell death)",
  "description": "The canonical preclinical tumor-growth-inhibition model. Proliferating tumor x1 grows exponential-to-linear; drug at concentration E damages proliferating cells at rate k2*E, and damaged cells traverse a signal-distribution transit chain x2->x3->x4 (first-order rate k1) before dying, producing delayed cell death. Observed tumor weight w = x1+x2+x3+x4. Values are illustrative xenograft-scale (mouse, 1/day, grams, concentration in ng/mL) and unverified. PRECLINICAL: applying to humans is the translation gap (see preclinical_translation.ivive_potency) and floors to D.",
